KEY DATASETS DATA_151.title: Key datasets data_1.5.1 element schema
KEY DATASETS DATA_151.description: Key datasets data_1.5.1 element schema generated by the CEDAR Template Editor 2.7.1

propertyDescriptions.measurement_method: Method used to capture the data measurements.
propertyDescriptions.measurement_method_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the method used to capture the data measurements.
propertyDescriptions.time_extent_start: The earliest year of data collection.
propertyDescriptions.time_extent_end: The last year of data collection; if ongoing and frequently updated, enter "Current" and if not frequently updated, include latest year available and update regularly.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution: The finest available temporal resolution (i.e., highest frequency, finest scale) from CV (# - preferred data).
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution: The finest spatial resolution of the data. If there are multiple resources and determining the finest spatial resolution is impractical, use "Other".
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the finest spatial resolution of the dataset. It may be a specific distance measure (e.g., '5 km’, ‘2 degrees’, ‘2 degrees by 5 degrees’). Convert resolutions like 40 deg. 11.25 min. to 40 degrees, 11 arc min, 25 arc sec.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_coverage: Maximum spatial coverage of the data; if specific regions, list in next field.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_bounding_box: Boundary coordinates for the geographical region (should be included in the model spatial metadata).
propertyDescriptions.geometry_type: Type of geometric data, the file extension will be different for different types (# - preferred data).
propertyDescriptions.geometry_source: Source or provider of the geometry data.
propertyDescriptions.model_methods: If data are modeled, description of modeling approaches used to generate them.
propertyDescriptions.exposure_media: The media to which the phenomena is related.
propertyDescriptions.geographic_feature: The type of geographic feature associated with the data.
propertyDescriptions.geographic_feature_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the type of geographic feature associated with the data.
propertyDescriptions.measures: List of specific variables collected by the system. If the variables are part of a set of variables then the set name can be provided, e.g., clinical labs for clinical laboratory tests especially if the specific labs vary from individual to individual, or VOC for a list of volatile organic chemicals. Copy measure terms from 'measure_list file'.
propertyDescriptions.Measures_other: If term is not in 'measures_list file' e.g., not part of VOC, enter it here for discussion with others about incorporation into VOC.
propertyDescriptions.model_methods_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the data modelling method(s) here.
propertyDescriptions.time_available_comment: Description of the time extent details if multiple times exist in the resource or if there are discontinuities over time.
propertyDescriptions.data_formats: Format of data download files (# - preferred data)
propertyDescriptions.spatial_coverage_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter spatial coverage region here; avoid using special symbols following same convention as in spatial_resolution_other (e.g., convert 40° to 40 degrees.). Do not convert latitude, longitude pairs if given as decimal.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the the temporal resolution here, e.g., one year daily average.
propertyDescriptions.geometry_source_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the geometry source here.
propertyDescriptions.license_type: License needed for using the dataset.
propertyDescriptions.license_type_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the type of license needed to use the dataset.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution_comment: Any relevant details describing the temporal resolution of the dataset, e.g., differences in temporal resolution among variables or climatology variables (20-year hourly data averages)
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution_comment: Any other relevant details describing the spatial resolution of the dataset, such as variable spatial resolution (e.g., nested grids), or grids with less common geometry (hexagonal grid, 0.5 degree x 0.625 degree, etc.).
propertyDescriptions.use_suggested: Suggested, intended, or applied use(s) in environmental and public health research based on example use applications and the data-provider's documentation on intended uses. (# = preferred).
propertyDescriptions.use_suggested_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the suggested use(s) here.
propertyDescriptions.use_key_variables: Brief description of the specific variables used in the example application(s).
propertyDescriptions.suggested_audience: Suggested audience to use this resource.
propertyDescriptions.use_strengths: Key strengths of the dataset for the suggested use(s).
propertyDescriptions.use_limitations: Key limitations or restrictions for the suggested use(s).
propertyDescriptions.use_example_metrics: Example metrics derived from example applications, that can be calculated using the dataset to assess individuals' (e.g., patients, health cohort participants) environmental exposures based on geocoded addresses and time period of exposure.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution_all_other_available: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter all other spatial resolutions not in CV, such as value and unit of measure, e.g., 50 km, 1 degree, 0.75 sq. km.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution_all_other_available: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter all other temporal resolutions for the dataset.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution_all_available: All available temporal resolutions (i.e., scale or frequency) of the dataset, such as daily or annual, selected from a CV.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution_all_available: All available horizontal spatial resolutions of the dataset, such as 1-km grid or ZIP codes, from CV. Use "Other" for spatial resolutions not included in the CV.
